-- Grilli Says No Plans for More Austerity Measures in Italy
-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 2012-09-15T12:19:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-15/grilli-says-no-plans-for-more-austerity-measures-in-italy.html
Finance Minister  Vittorio Grilli 
said Italy has no plans to introduce further austerity measures
to tackle the budget deficit.  While the recession is affecting the budget in nominal
terms, structural deficit targets are still on track, he told
reporters in Nicosia, Cyprus today after meeting European
finance chiefs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
